==English==
===Etymology===
From '''micro''' (small) + '''[[organism]]'''
===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /ˌmai.kɹo.ˈɔɹ.ɡɐ̆.nɪ.zm̩/
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# organisms, usu. single-celled, that are too small to be seen by the unaided eye. [[Bacteria]], [[protist]]s, [[fungus|fungi]] are considered microorganisms.

===Translations===
*Danish: [[mikroorganisme]]
*Frisian: [[mikro-organisme]]

